Around 150 firefighters battled a major blaze on the roof of a Moscow apartment building early on Thursday and used a helicopter to try to douse the flames, news agencies and eyewitnesses said. About 400 people were evacuated from the nine-storey building on Leninsky Prospekt, a major avenue just to the southwest of the downtown core, a spokesperson for Russiaâ€™s federal emergencies ministry told RIA and Tass agencies. At just before 1 am local time (2200 GMT on Wednesday) the fire covered an area of about 1 000 square meters, the spokesperson added. At one point a helicopter could be seen dropping water from a large bucket onto the flames. There was no immediate word on the cause of the fire. 